00:40:28,236 --> 00:40:31,236
It was simply my desire to talk.

495
00:40:33,740 --> 00:40:36,278
Well, I have to go.

496
00:40:36,576 --> 00:40:41,736
I'll leave the poems on your doorstep. Give Marianne my regards.

497
00:40:42,915 --> 00:40:48,419
I will stick by you through thick and thin.

498
00:40:48,712 --> 00:40:49,875
Bye!

499
00:40:51,006 --> 00:40:56,629
See you around 12:30. Bye.

500
00:40:57,971 --> 00:41:01,220
I'm sorry I kept you waiting.

501
00:41:02,308 --> 00:41:08,061
It is usually during this first encounter that we identify the problem.

502
00:41:08,355 --> 00:41:10,063
I want a divorce.

503
00:41:10,357 --> 00:41:14,105
- How long have you been married? - More than 20 years.

504
00:41:14,402 --> 00:41:19,064
- Do you have a job? - No, I'm a housewife.

505
00:41:19,365 --> 00:41:22,366
Why do you want a divorce?

506
00:41:29,541 --> 00:41:32,707
It is a loveless marriage.

507
00:41:33,002 --> 00:41:37,130
- Is that your reason? - Yes.

508
00:41:37,423 --> 00:41:44,173
- Has it always been like this? - Yes, for the entire 20 years.

509
00:41:45,139 --> 00:41:48,757
But now you want to break free.

510
00:41:50,227 --> 00:41:51,425
Yes.

511
00:41:53,271 --> 00:42:00,068
My husband is a responsible man. He is kind and conscientious.

512
00:42:00,903 --> 00:42:05,730
He was an excellent father. We never argued.

513
00:42:06,033 --> 00:42:11,905
We have a beautiful apartment and a house in the countryside.

514
00:42:13,456 --> 00:42:15,864
We are both passionate about music.

515
00:42:16,167 --> 00:42:20,117
We belong to a chamber music society.

516
00:42:20,421 --> 00:42:24,917
- That all sounds ideal. - Yes, doesn't it?

517
00:42:25,217 --> 00:42:29,879
But there is no love between us, there never has been.

518
00:42:31,139 --> 00:42:36,346
Forgive me for asking, but have you met anyone?

519
00:42:38,896 --> 00:42:40,520
No I haven't.

520
00:42:40,731 --> 00:42:42,605
What about your husband?

521
00:42:42,900 --> 00:42:45,474
Not as far as I know.

522
00:42:45,778 --> 00:42:48,613
Won't it be lonely for you?

523
00:42:48,906 --> 00:42:52,108
I think so...

524
00:42:52,409 --> 00:42:53,951
But that's better

525
00:42:54,160 --> 00:42:56,781
than living in a loveless marriage.

526
00:42:59,749 --> 00:43:03,829
Have you informed your husband about this?

527
00:43:04,128 --> 00:43:05,871
Naturally.

528
00:43:06,171 --> 00:43:08,330
15 years ago I told him

529
00:43:08,549 --> 00:43:12,712
I didn't want to live with him.

530
00:43:13,011 --> 00:43:14,802
He asked me to wait

531
00:43:15,013 --> 00:43:17,800
until the children grew up.

532
00:43:18,099 --> 00:43:21,598
Now that they have left their homes,

533
00:43:21,894 --> 00:43:24,930
I can get a divorce.

534
00:43:25,230 --> 00:43:27,768
And what does he say?

535
00:43:29,193 --> 00:43:36,025
He constantly asks me what's wrong with our marriage.

536
00:43:36,324 --> 00:43:38,530
I tell him I can't go on

537
00:43:38,743 --> 00:43:42,277
in a relationship that lacks love.

538
00:43:42,579 --> 00:43:47,822
Then he asks what this love should consist of.

539
00:43:48,126 --> 00:43:50,333
But I can't describe it

540
00:43:50,629 --> 00:43:53,748
something that doesn't exist.

541
00:43:54,048 --> 00:43:58,840
Did you get along well with your children?

542
00:43:59,970 --> 00:44:02,888
I never loved my children.

543
00:44:03,807 --> 00:44:05,800
I know that now...

544
00:44:06,101 --> 00:44:10,015
I used to think I had that. People do.

545
00:44:10,313 --> 00:44:12,021
But I know now

546
00:44:12,232 --> 00:44:14,188
that I never loved her.

547
00:44:14,484 --> 00:44:17,899
Nevertheless, I was a good mother to her.

548
00:44:18,195 --> 00:44:21,480
I did everything I could, although

549
00:44:21,698 --> 00:44:24,734
I never felt anything for her.

550
00:44:30,915 --> 00:44:33,916
I know exactly what you’re thinking:

551
00:44:35,587 --> 00:44:39,963
“She was spoiled and has no sense of humor.”

552
00:44:41,091 --> 00:44:43,380
She has everything she could ever wish for,

553
00:44:43,677 --> 00:44:48,339
but she still complains about love.

554
00:44:48,640 --> 00:44:50,680
There are other qualities:

555
00:44:50,892 --> 00:44:53,561
“Friendship, loyalty, security…”

556
00:44:53,853 --> 00:44:56,771
Something like that, yes.

557
00:45:00,234 --> 00:45:03,318
Let me tell you something.

558
00:45:04,696 --> 00:45:07,021
I have a mental image of myself,

559
00:45:07,824 --> 00:45:12,320
which does not correspond to reality.

560
00:45:12,620 --> 00:45:17,080
Forgive me for a personal question...

561
00:45:19,877 --> 00:45:23,292
Isn't it true that love...

562
00:45:27,550 --> 00:45:28,961
What did you want to ask?

563
00:45:30,178 --> 00:45:33,677
I'm not sure. Forgive me.

564
00:45:39,603 --> 00:45:43,601
I have the ability to love.

565
00:45:46,234 --> 00:45:53,031
But it was all... bottled.

566
00:45:56,035 --> 00:46:01,325
The life I've been living has stifled my potential.

567
00:46:02,415 --> 00:46:05,701
It's time to change that.

568
00:46:06,003 --> 00:46:08,078
The first step is divorce.

569
00:46:08,379 --> 00:46:11,913
My husband and I

570
00:46:12,217 --> 00:46:14,754
block each other in a deadly way.

571
00:46:15,053 --> 00:46:17,045
That sounds scary.

572
00:46:18,347 --> 00:46:21,348
It's scary.

573
00:46:22,183 --> 00:46:25,552
Something strange happens.

574
00:46:25,854 --> 00:46:30,432
My senses, sight, hearing, touch

575
00:46:30,733 --> 00:46:32,772
are starting to let me down.

576
00:46:33,068 --> 00:46:34,978
This table for example

577
00:46:35,279 --> 00:46:38,979
I can see and touch it...

578
00:46:39,283 --> 00:46:41,524
But the sensation

579
00:46:41,826 --> 00:46:45,776
is reduced and dry.

580
00:46:46,080 --> 00:46:48,915
Do you understand?

581
00:46:51,461 --> 00:46:53,832
I think so.

582
00:46:54,129 --> 00:46:56,964
It's the same with everything -

583
00:46:57,258 --> 00:47:03,426
Music, scents, faces and voices.

584
00:47:03,722 --> 00:47:05,797
Everything seems...

585
00:47:06,098 --> 00:47:11,603
puny, grey and undignified.

586
00:47:12,563 --> 00:47:17,225
Now there is something to drink and eat.

587
00:47:17,568 --> 00:47:22,443
Sitting on an empty stomach is fatal.

588
00:47:22,739 --> 00:47:26,688
Do you remember when we participated in the May Day procession?

589
00:47:26,993 --> 00:47:29,828
You were the more ardent believer.

590
00:47:30,120 --> 00:47:33,454
You told me I neglected our home.

591
00:47:33,749 --> 00:47:37,961
That was the winter we all got sick from the Asian flu.

592
00:47:38,253 --> 00:47:44,374
- Back then, we believed in the future. - It's nice to believe in something.

593
00:47:44,676 --> 00:47:49,716
And we had the pleasure of annoying our parents.

594
00:47:50,013 --> 00:47:54,390
- You were a hothead. - So was your father.

595
00:47:54,685 --> 00:47:58,433
Quite a hothead. As a socialist, you were very attractive.

596
00:47:58,730 --> 00:48:03,890
Am I not very attractive now?

597
00:48:04,194 --> 00:48:07,313
But married people lose interest in each other.

598
00:48:08,739 --> 00:48:12,155
We don't have that.

599
00:48:12,868 --> 00:48:17,329
We simply have too much to do and are completely exhausted in the evenings.

600
00:48:17,623 --> 00:48:21,751
That wasn't an accusation, I promise.

601
00:48:22,043 --> 00:48:27,879
- We like each other. - Not like that.

602
00:48:28,174 --> 00:48:32,717
- Oh yes, we do. - Our lives are full of excuses.

603
00:48:33,012 --> 00:48:37,839
It's not my fault that I don't enjoy it as much as I used to.

604
00:48:38,141 --> 00:48:43,645
There's a natural explanation. You shouldn't blame me.

605
00:48:43,938 --> 00:48:48,481
- Don't get upset. - We have a great sex life.

606
00:48:48,775 --> 00:48:55,229
We're not as passionate these days, but it could be worse.

607
00:48:55,532 --> 00:48:59,232
Sex isn't everything.

608
00:48:59,536 --> 00:49:04,245
If you are not satisfied, find a lover

609
00:49:04,540 --> 00:49:07,411
who is more sexually exciting.

610
00:49:07,710 --> 00:49:11,078
- I assure you, I'll do my best! - Right...

611
00:49:15,550 --> 00:49:17,958
You have that look again.

612
00:49:18,261 --> 00:49:22,259
Tell me what you're thinking about.

613
00:49:22,557 --> 00:49:27,681
- You're just getting angry. - No, I'm listening.

614
00:49:27,978 --> 00:49:32,272
Why make sex so complicated?

615
00:49:32,565 --> 00:49:35,103
It's pretty basic stuff.

616
00:49:35,401 --> 00:49:39,648
It has become a sore point.

617
00:49:39,947 --> 00:49:42,948
It's all your mother's fault.

618
00:49:43,243 --> 00:49:47,785
- You're so superficial. - You're a grump!

619
00:49:48,080 --> 00:49:50,750
You blame me for everything.

620
00:49:51,041 --> 00:49:55,085
- You said you'd do your best. - I am!

621
00:49:55,379 --> 00:49:57,537
This is absurd!

622
00:49:57,839 --> 00:50:01,338
Are you calling me a liar?

623
00:50:01,634 --> 00:50:04,256
Then what are you talking about?

624
00:50:04,554 --> 00:50:08,171
Let's leave that and go to bed.

625
00:50:08,473 --> 00:50:12,553
It's typical of you to upset me so

626
00:50:12,853 --> 00:50:16,685
and then yawn and say it's bedtime.

627
00:50:18,191 --> 00:50:22,058
They suffer from unbridled ambition.

628
00:50:22,362 --> 00:50:25,695
We often joke about

629
00:50:25,990 --> 00:50:30,984
but can't our miserable sex life be spared?

630
00:50:31,286 --> 00:50:34,286
Why don't you leave me alone?

631
00:50:34,581 --> 00:50:37,250
First you attack me because I don't try

632
00:50:37,459 --> 00:50:39,996
and later for the effort.

633
00:50:40,294 --> 00:50:41,409
And now look what I did!

634
00:50:41,712 --> 00:50:43,586
Yes, you actually did.

635
00:50:51,263 --> 00:50:54,714
Couldn't you be kind instead?

636
00:50:55,016 --> 00:51:00,093
Well, well... Don't be sad. I'm sorry.

637
00:51:00,396 --> 00:51:05,473
You know, you can talk too much about these things.

638
00:51:05,776 --> 00:51:09,774
I know you shouldn’t keep secrets,

639
00:51:10,072 --> 00:51:13,939
but in this case the rule is wrong.

640
00:51:14,242 --> 00:51:19,402
There are some things you shouldn't snoop into.

641
00:51:19,706 --> 00:51:26,040
We hurt each other endlessly

642
00:51:26,337 --> 00:51:30,417
and the barbs are still there when we go to bed.

643
00:51:30,716 --> 00:51:33,835
It's like lying on a bed of nails.

644
00:51:35,136 --> 00:51:37,806
- What are you laughing about? - The nail bed.

645
00:51:38,514 --> 00:51:42,429
- Laughter is all well and good. - Let's go to bed.

646
00:51:42,727 --> 00:51:46,095
They were incredibly tactless.

647
00:51:46,396 --> 00:51:48,769
I apologize.

648
00:51:50,609 --> 00:51:53,609
Don't I give you enough affection?

649
00:51:53,903 --> 00:51:56,062
Affection takes time.

650
00:51:56,364 --> 00:52:02,568
- Then you're not getting enough. - We're not getting enough, and we're not giving enough either.

651
00:52:02,870 --> 00:52:06,998
That's why I wanted us to go away this summer.

652
00:52:07,291 --> 00:52:11,786
Affection should not be saved for vacation.

653
00:52:12,086 --> 00:52:14,494
You're nice even if you're an idiot.

654
00:52:14,797 --> 00:52:17,419
Luckily, I'm married to you.

655
00:52:17,717 --> 00:52:23,091
You're mediocre, but you have your moments of greatness.

656
00:52:24,807 --> 00:52:29,350
At our age, thousands of brain cells burn out every day.

657
00:52:29,644 --> 00:52:36,263
- Never to be replaced... - You must lose a million!

658
00:52:38,027 --> 00:52:43,981
You're incredibly sweet anyway, even when you swear and make a fuss.

659
00:52:45,993 --> 00:52:49,112
I've almost fallen asleep.

660
00:52:49,412 --> 00:52:55,865
- I'm just checking on the kids. - I'm almost asleep, so don't worry.

661
00:53:07,012 --> 00:53:10,961
Don't you want to set the alarm?

662
00:53:17,062 --> 00:53:21,012
If you want, you can sleep with me now.

663
00:53:21,316 --> 00:53:24,685
Thanks for the offer, but I'm too tired.

664
00:54:10,027 --> 00:54:15,733
Already here? I wasn't expecting you until tomorrow.

665
00:54:16,033 --> 00:54:21,537
What a nice surprise! Are you hungry?

666
00:54:21,830 --> 00:54:24,866
We all went to bed early.

667
00:54:25,167 --> 00:54:31,667
We thought we'd go to bed early. The girls and I were on a diet.

668
00:54:31,964 --> 00:54:36,922
- Would you like some sandwiches? - Sounds good to me.

669
00:54:37,220 --> 00:54:42,640
Or should I fry you some eggs and ham or make you some soup?

670
00:54:42,933 --> 00:54:45,637
No, sandwiches and beer are perfectly sufficient.

671
00:54:45,935 --> 00:54:49,850
By the way, Peter and Katarina will call you on Monday.

672
00:54:50,148 --> 00:54:54,192
What an ordeal they are going through!

673
00:54:54,485 --> 00:54:58,019
They don't seem to be able to agree on their divorce.

674
00:54:58,322 --> 00:55:04,407
I told them they should each get a lawyer, but they don't want to.

675
00:55:04,703 --> 00:55:08,486
Listen, put on your pajamas and I'll bring in a tray.

676
00:55:08,789 --> 00:55:11,245
Sounds good...

677
00:55:11,542 --> 00:55:15,077
I was afraid you would be angry with me.

678
00:55:15,379 --> 00:55:20,455
- Why should I? - I was horrible on the phone.

679
00:55:21,843 --> 00:55:25,509
I called back, but you had pulled the plug.

680
00:55:25,722 --> 00:55:28,010
I was tired last night.

681
00:55:28,307 --> 00:55:32,056
I was with that idiot from the ministry.

682
00:55:32,353 --> 00:55:37,477
These bureaucratic idiots who are responsible for our well-being...

683
00:55:37,775 --> 00:55:42,436
- I still think I behaved badly. - Let's drop the subject.

684
00:55:42,737 --> 00:55:46,605
You never want to stop talking,

685
00:55:46,908 --> 00:55:49,445
but that won't last long, dear.

686
00:55:49,744 --> 00:55:55,912
I just wanted to say that you were right, but so was I.

687
00:55:56,208 --> 00:56:01,997
If you don't want to wear a tuxedo, that's your business.

688
00:56:02,297 --> 00:56:09,213
- But I have a right to my own opinion. - I hate wearing a tuxedo.

689
00:56:09,512 --> 00:56:15,051
It's a ridiculous outfit. I feel like a chimpanzee in disguise.

690
00:56:15,351 --> 00:56:17,426
Let's not start arguing.

691
00:56:17,728 --> 00:56:20,479
Tuxedo or not, I love you.

692
00:56:20,772 --> 00:56:24,105
A tuxedo is hardly necessary for our marriage.

693
00:56:24,401 --> 00:56:28,861
- That's how it seemed to me last night. - I said I was wrong.

694
00:56:35,619 --> 00:56:39,664
When I watch you eat, I get hungry...

695
00:56:41,916 --> 00:56:45,332
I need a sandwich.

696
00:56:46,670 --> 00:56:50,254
I'm so hungry, I feel dizzy.

697
00:56:50,549 --> 00:56:57,512
I've lost almost two kilos this week. Is it noticeable?

698
00:56:57,806 --> 00:57:00,261
However, I can feel it.

699
00:57:00,559 --> 00:57:03,974
But sometimes it seems pointless...

700
00:57:04,270 --> 00:57:08,482
Why should we deny ourselves the good things in life?

701
00:57:08,774 --> 00:57:13,103
Why can't we be fat and happy?

702
00:57:13,404 --> 00:57:16,404
Do you remember Aunt Miriam and Uncle David?

703
00:57:16,698 --> 00:57:19,450
They were tall, fat and cheerful.

704
00:57:19,742 --> 00:57:25,863
They slept holding hands in their double bed.

705
00:57:26,166 --> 00:57:31,586
Happy with each other, just as they were.

706
00:57:31,878 --> 00:57:35,497
Why can’t we be like them,

707
00:57:35,799 --> 00:57:38,883
full of satisfaction?

708
00:57:40,220 --> 00:57:42,212
What's up?

709
00:57:42,513 --> 00:57:45,218
Are you angry?

710
00:57:46,559 --> 00:57:49,513
Something happened?

711
00:57:49,812 --> 00:57:51,769
What's up?

712
00:57:53,274 --> 00:57:55,231
Tell me.

713
00:57:59,946 --> 00:58:03,362
I came here to tell you something.

714
00:58:07,912 --> 00:58:11,744
I went there and fell in love.

715
00:58:12,041 --> 00:58:17,627
It's pretty absurd and probably completely wrong...

716
00:58:21,299 --> 00:58:25,427
I met her at this conference in June.

717
00:58:26,763 --> 00:58:29,217
She was an interpreter.

718
00:58:29,515 --> 00:58:34,639
She studies Slavic studies.

719
00:58:38,147 --> 00:58:40,639
She's not particularly nice to look at.

720
00:58:40,942 --> 00:58:44,774
You might even find them ugly.

721
00:58:46,447 --> 00:58:50,065
I have no idea what this will lead to.

722
00:58:50,367 --> 00:58:54,199
I don't know anything. I'm confused.

723
00:58:58,875 --> 00:59:01,200
On a certain level I am happy

724
00:59:01,503 --> 00:59:04,622
but I feel so guilty towards you and the girls.

725
00:59:04,922 --> 00:59:08,504
We always got along so well.

726
00:59:10,803 --> 00:59:15,014
Things were neither better nor worse

727
00:59:15,307 --> 00:59:18,307
than in most families.

728
00:59:22,814 --> 00:59:26,147
Say something, for heaven's sake.

729
00:59:27,860 --> 00:59:31,608
I don't know what to say.

730
00:59:34,240 --> 00:59:38,903
It was wrong not to tell you sooner,

731
00:59:39,204 --> 00:59:44,363
but I thought I would get over it.

732
00:59:44,666 --> 00:59:47,453
I didn't mean to alarm you.

733
00:59:48,462 --> 00:59:50,335
It's funny...

734
00:59:54,217 --> 00:59:57,218
...that I didn't notice anything.

735
00:59:57,512 --> 01:00:03,052
Everything was as usual.

736
01:00:03,351 --> 01:00:07,348
In fact, even better.

737
01:00:07,646 --> 01:00:09,888
You were so sweet.

738
01:00:10,190 --> 01:00:15,066
I was a stupid, blind fool.

739
01:00:15,362 --> 01:00:18,362
I didn't understand...

740
01:00:19,699 --> 01:00:22,984
- How humiliating. - No, you didn't understand anything.

741
01:00:23,202 --> 01:00:27,116
You have never been particularly attentive.

742
01:00:30,959 --> 01:00:35,585
- What happens next? - I don't know.

743
01:00:35,880 --> 01:00:37,672
Do you want a divorce?

744
01:00:37,966 --> 01:00:40,373
Will you marry her?

745
01:00:40,677 --> 01:00:47,046
Why are you telling me now? What's the rush?

746
01:00:54,731 --> 01:00:58,265
We're going to Paris tomorrow.

747
01:01:00,695 --> 01:01:05,356
I want to escape it all.

748
01:01:06,116 --> 01:01:10,576
I wanted to go there this fall anyway.

749
01:01:11,413 --> 01:01:15,411
Paula has this scholarship...

750
01:01:17,377 --> 01:01:19,868
..and I want to be with her.

751
01:01:20,171 --> 01:01:24,215
I can't do it without her.

752
01:01:24,508 --> 01:01:28,043
So we're leaving tomorrow.

753
01:01:33,558 --> 01:01:36,227
Now that I'm talking to you,

754
01:01:36,519 --> 01:01:39,639
I want to get rid of the whole damn thing.

755
01:01:39,939 --> 01:01:43,354
I am tired and scared.

